condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule 2-Section I,A,2 | Description :The Borrower shall, through the Ministry of Transport, establish andthereafter maintain a Steering Committee, with membership and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :01-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule1-Section II, B/1 | Description :The Borrower shall, through the Project Implementing Entity,maintain orcause to be maintained a financial management system in accordance with theprovisions of Section 5.09 of the GeneralConditions. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule1-Section II, B/2 | Description :The Borrower shall, through the Project Implementing Entity, prepareandfurnish to the Bank not later than forty five (45) days after the end of eachcalendar semester, interim unaudited financialreports for the Project covering thesemester, in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule1-Section II, B/3 | Description :The Borrower shall cause the Project Implementing Entity to have itsFinancialStatements and the financial statements reflecting the operations, resources andexpenditures related to the Projectaudited by the Borrower’s Central AuditingOrganization in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.09 (b) of theGeneralConditions. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule2-Section I,C | Description :The Borrower shall cause the Project Implementing Entity to ensure thatremedial measures are taken during the implementation and operation of the Project in accordance with the provisions set forth inthe ESIA and the EMP | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :LA-Schedule2-Section II,A | Description :The Borrower shall cause the Project Implementing Entity to monitor andevaluate the progress of the Project and prepare Reports in accordance with the provisions of Section 5.08 of the GC and onthe basis of the indicators agreed with the Bank. Each Reportshall cover the period of 1 calendar quarter, and shall be furnishedto the Bank not later than 45 days following the end of period | Frequency :Quarterly
Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,A,1 | Description :Creation of PMU | Due Date :30-Apr-2009
Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,A,1 | Description :Fully staffing PMU | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,A,3,a | Description :ENR shall enter a contract , on terms and conditions satisfactory tothe Bank, for supervision of signaling modernization works under component 1 of the Project; | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,A,3,b | Description :ENR shall enter a contract, on terms and conditions satisfactory tothe Bank, regarding the supervision of track renewal works under component 2 of the Project; | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,A,3,c | Description :ENR shall enter a two years long contract, on terms and conditionssatisfactory to the Bank, regarding the provision of technical assistance to the PMU. | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section I,C,2 | Description :ENR shall enter into a contract for the implementation of capacitystrengthening measures under the EMP with a qualified firm and on terms of reference all as acceptable to the Bank | Due Date:31-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section II, A-3b | Description :The Project Implementing Entity, shall prepare, and at least three(3) month prior to the Midterm Review, furnish to the Bank, a separate report describing the status of implementation of eachcomponent of the Project and a summary report of Project implementation generally (the “Mid-term Report”). | Due Date :30-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-Section II, A-4 | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall provide to the Borrower nolater than three months after the closing date, for incorporation in the report referred to in Section 5.08(c) of the GeneralConditions (Completion Report) all such information as the Borrower or the Bank shall reasonably request for the purposes of thatSection. | Due Date :30-Jun-2017

Finance Agreement :PA-Schedule-SectionI,A-2 | Description :For the purpose of carrying out the Project, the Project ImplementingEntity shall adoptprocedures satisfactory to the Bank to ensure that the consultants selected to carry outservices under theProject have the necessary professional qualifications and shall carryout their assignments in a timely manner and that the scopeof their services is consistentwith the needs of the Project. | Frequency :Yearly
